{"title":"Omar di Felice is Again Crossing Antarctica on a Prototype Wilier Fat Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/omar-di-felice-is-again-crossing-antarctica-on-a-prototype-wilier-fat-bike/","date":1700853699000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Italian ultradistance cyclist Omar di Felice is 5 days into an estimated 2 months to cross Antarctica on his own by fat bike, fighting some of the harshest conditions on the planet. It is an ambitious adventure project aiming to draw attention to the issue of climate change. And he knows how difficult it will be, having to be evacuated on his first attempt last December. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But he’s back, and making headway. Riding an aluminum prototype fat bike built for him by Wilier, and pulling a sled with all the food, fuel, shelter, and extreme weather gear to survive the windswept frozen landscape…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Antarctica Unlimited: A solo crossing of Antarctica by fat bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting at sea level from Hercules Inlet, Omar di Felice plans to ride roughly 1100km climbing up to the South Pole, then will descend down to the Leverett Glacier, before ultimately climbing back up to the pole for a total 1600km distance. We can all easily grasp that the extreme weather will be windy, cold, and with white-out conditions likely. It is Antarctica after all. But we easily overlook the elevation gain, while hauling all the necessary gear. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition in 24hr daylight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_perpetual-daylight.jpg 1000w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/omardifelice\" target=\"_blank\">Omar di Felice</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mirrormedia.art\" target=\"_blank\">Mirror Media</a>) </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Immediately, leaving base camp at Hercules Inlet, Omar climbed 800m in the first 30km, while of course riding a heavy fat bike loaded with gear AND pulling a sled / ski pulk laden with everything he could need for a couple of months alone. Then, he faced the same elevation to climb again, instead skirting the mountains for another forty kilometers, before continuing the ascent to the South Pole which sits at 2835m above where he started.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Unexpected obstacle crossing Antarctica by fat bike</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, sunny day\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_blue-skies-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once cold, wind &amp; elevation are overcome, the next major obstacle is very much psychological. Because it definitely isn’t always sunny.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, view from inside the tent on a clear day\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent-297x238.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent-800x640.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_view-from-inside-the-tent-768x614.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The physical effort is something you can train for. As is the solo self-supported aspect. Omar di Felice did win the 6800km Trans America Bike Race this summer after all. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But in December in Antarctica, the sun doesn’t set. Stuck in a storm, you may spend days sheltered inside your tent with no visible passage of time. That happened <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/omar-di-felices-prototype-wilier-fat-bike-to-ride-longest-bicycle-journey-across-antarctica/\">last year</a> for 3 days of whiteout conditions, that literally broke Omar mentally, leaving him alone sleep-deprived with his thoughts in never-ending daylight. Past trauma returned, in what could probably be described as a walking nightmare. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ultimately, he realized that he couldn’t safely continue, even after the storm subsided. So the support team evacuated Omar, early into the attempt. But he vowed to come back again.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>So what has changed, with Omar and his prototype Wilier fat bike setup?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, complete bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_complete-fatbike-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Obviously, now Omar Di Felice knows more what he was getting into. Beyond the psychical prep, he’s more ready for the unique mental test as well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As for his bike, not that much has changed really. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1050\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, custom painted frameset detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail-297x156.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail-800x420.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail-120x63.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail-768x403.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_frameset-detail-1536x806.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We last had caught up with his <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/omar-di-felices-prototype-wilier-fat-bike-to-ride-longest-bicycle-journey-across-antarctica/\" target=\"_blank\">raw aluminum prototype fat bike</a>, produced as a one-off project from sponsor Wilier.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins.jpg\" alt=\"Warming Stripes by climate scientist Ed Hawkins\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins-297x46.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins-800x125.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins-120x19.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Warming-strips-by-climate-scientist-Ed-Hawkins-768x120.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But even for last year’s expedition, they had custom painted the bike and its matching alloy fork in the “<a href=\"https://www.science.org/content/article/new-climate-stripes-reveal-how-much-hotter-your-hometown-has-gotten-past-century\" target=\"_blank\">Warming Stripes</a>” graphic of climate scientist <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/climatehawkins/\" target=\"_blank\">Ed Hawkins</a> from the #ShowYourStripes campaign. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, frame &amp; Miss Grape bags detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_bike-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Each of the blue &amp; red barcode stripes represents a year of deviation from the climate average for the last 160 years, with the red warming of the past 22 years quite obvious.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Antarctic Expedition hauling </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, ready for adventure\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_ready-to-set-off-Hercules-Inlet-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the custom bike Omar fits a set of custom made Miss Grape bags, including a custom full frame bag and a new long Big Node toptube bag for more ready access storage. Plus, a couple of Trunk 6 Waterproof bags on each fork leg.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"860\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, pulk sled\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled-800x459.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_Fjellpulken-Xplorer-expedition-pulk-sled-768x440.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The majority of Omar’s 90kg of gear though, is packed inside a new customized Norwegian sled, the <a href=\"https://www.fjellpulken.com/ekspedisjonspulk\">Fjellpulken Xplorer</a> expedition pulk. But the on-bike bags from <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=missgrape\" target=\"_blank\">Miss Grape</a> provide quicker access. Get to key gear to deal with fast changing weather, to maintain proper nutrition. And to set camp as quickly as possible once he stops riding.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech Details &amp; Bike Setup</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, MissGrape cockpit management\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_cockpit-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A Garmin InReach system handles navigation. And he mounts it to a Miss Grape Ilcoso combination extension bar and bar bag holder, off of his handlebar. He’s also newly using a Iridium Go Exec modem and solar panel recharging. That brings better communications with basecamp, and the ability to send live photos like these we have from the current expedition.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, Shimano XT LinkGlide\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Shimano-XT-LinkGlide-drivetrain-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Drivetrain is upgrade to XT. But it’s still the uniquely durable thicker Shimano XT <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-shimano-deore-xt-linkglide-is-3x-more-durable-not-backwards-compatible/\" target=\"_blank\">LinkGlide</a> 11-speed system (in 12sp spacing) with a wide 11-50T cassette.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, Selle San Marco Aspide saddle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_Selle-San-Marco-saddle-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And he tops it off with a new ti-railed Selle San Marco Aspide Short Supercomfort saddle. Because he’s going to spend a lot of time sitting on this thing going slow for the next several weeks. Plus, ESI Chunky grips.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, packing for th etrip\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_packing-prep-work-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Officially, Continental tires and Mavic wheels sponsor Omar. But since neither make fatbike kit, he’s rolling on stealthily blacked-out kit. DT Swiss <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dt-swiss-takes-on-fat-bikes-with-new-big-ride-2250-classic-wheelset/\" target=\"_blank\">BR 2250</a> wheels and 27.5 x 4.0″ 45NRTH <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-45nrths-dillinger-5-fat-bike-tires-rob-the-bank-but-may-be-worth-doing-the-time/\" target=\"_blank\">Dillinger</a> 4 studded tires.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, photo by Mirror Media, training\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_photo-by-MirrorMedia_training-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Follow along live, now</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition.jpg\"><img width=\"2060\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition.jpg\" alt=\"Omar di Felice Antarctica Unlimited solo crossing by fat bike, fatbike expedition for climate change awareness, route plan map with contours\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition.jpg 2060w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-297x216.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-800x583.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-120x87.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-768x559.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-1536x1118.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Omar-di-Felice-Antarctica-Unlimited-solo-crossing-by-fat-bike_solo-antartica-crossing-expedition-2048x1491.jpg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(Map/ESA)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And now we just have to cross out fingers, follow-along, and wait.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow Omar di Felice’s live position via <a href=\"https://live.endu.net/antarcticaunlimited/\" target=\"_blank\">ENDUlive</a>. It’s relatively slow-going in the ultra-distance dotwatching scheme of things. But we are enthralled.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/omar-di-felice-is-again-crossing-antarctica-on-a-prototype-wilier-fat-bike/\">Omar di Felice is Again Crossing Antarctica on a Prototype Wilier Fat Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"4179f07551ba1b3b6156ec13260ce3da6404aec322edf5610246b2d60f1a159e","category":"Cycling"}